author: hwright
msg: Make the dump editor baton self-contained.  That is, set some output values
by reference, rather than by value.  This is needed when using the Ev2 shims,
since the shims change the editor baton, and *not* doing this results in
part of the library working with the new baton as if it were the old one,
leading to interesting results.
Current number of Ev2 test failures: 576
* subversion/libsvn_repos/dump.c
(edit_baton): Make some output values pointers instead of values.
(dump_nodes): Set the output value by reference, if wanted.
(get_dump_editor): Take the new references to be used, and store them in the
edit baton.
(svn_repos_dump_fs3): Provide the output value references to
get_dump_editor().
(svn_repos_verify_fs2): Provide NULL values for these parameters (since we
don't care about them in this context).
